    • Account

      public Account(String acctName, byte[] passwordHash, int balance, String holderName) throws AccountException
      Constructor, validates length of account name and the initial balance.
      Parameters:
      acctName - the account name
      passwordHash - the password hash
      balance - the balance
      holderName - the name of the account holder
      Throws:
      AccountException - if the account name is too short or balance too low

  • Method Details

    • registerAccountManager

      public void registerAccountManager(AccountManager accountManager)
      Sets the account manager responsible for persisting/managing this account. This may be invoked exactly once on any given account, any subsequent invocations should be ignored.
      Parameters:
      accountManager - the account manager

    • setName

      public void setName(String acctName) throws AccountException
      Sets the account name. The name will be checked for minimum length MIN_ACCT_LEN..

      This operation is not generally used but is provided for JavaBean conformance.

      Parameters:
      acctName - the value to be set for the account name
      Throws:
      AccountException - if the account name is to short

    • reflectOrder

      public void reflectOrder(Order order, int executionPrice)
      Incorporates the effect of an order in the balance. Increments or decrements the account balance by the execution price * number of shares in the order and then persists the account, using the account manager.
      Parameters:
      order - the order to be reflected in the account
      executionPrice - the price the order was executed at
